Code III B-1
April 8, 1936

(1)
West Street, north from Warren Street, showing foundation work for the extension of the West Side Express Highway. For an account of same, see the New York Times of November 12, 1937. The hotel seen on the right is the Northwestern, No. 184-85 West Street, at the S.E. corner of Chambers Street.

July 28, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, one block northward (Chambers Street). Note on the left Pier No. 21 North River, at the foot of Duane Street.

July 28, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
The same, slightly northward (Duane Street).
